originalText.text: Wonderful living here. The location is between an express and local trains (96th and 86th St stations). The location and building are super safe. The doorman are outstanding!!! Do not listen to the review below me giving 1-star (that person is just upset bc they do not how to manage living in NYC). I would absolutely live here again if I get the chance to be back in NYC.

originalText.text: We all know how difficult finding a great apartment in Manhattan can be.  I feel so lucky that my experience in Stonehenge Tower has been very positive in so many ways.  How did I find the perfect apt in a great neighborhood and in such a well run building?   It started with Stonehenge and their no fee policy which was much appreciated.  The efficient management team moved the process along and very quickly I was settled into my new home.   My apt is bright, spacious and with great closets.  The super, Russ, is very responsive and the building is kept very clean.   Being a dog friendly building is also a big plus for me.  The doormen are very personable and welcoming; making for a safe environment to come back to everyday.  I’m also impressed with the sense of community the Stonehenge team tries to foster with events at different buildings.   I have been here four months and am writing this review hoping it is helpful to others.

originalText.text: I would say it's really a nice experience to live here. Great location with an acceptable price. Doorman remembers all the people living here and will tell you when your package arrives. (in my previous renting experience in other apartments I always needed to say who I am, my unit number). A lot of nice restaurants are nearby and also 1 train will connect you to everywhere in NYC.

originalText.text: Highly recommend this building！ Leticia and Russ work for that building and they are super helpful and the most kind person I have ever seen. The doormen are always friendly. I rented a alcove studio-- it's super spacious and well structured.   A bonus living here --an awesome Italian restaurant Cibo E Vino is just around the corner;)

originalText.text: I really enjoyed living here, albeit short. The building is great and safe. It's in a good location and close to the 1,2,3, Trader Joe's, Bed Bath & Beyond, Duane Reade, a ton of restaurants. Columbus Square is only 10 blocks up and has a Whole Foods, TJ Max, Home Goods, and other stores. It's close to Central Park and Riverside Park. The doormen are the best! I had a really good experience and would highly recommend.
